To my shock and apparently nobody else’s Conor was able to gain 7+ pounds in 4 days or less  and weigh in officially at 170 pounds and from what I saw was not fat. This was my first red flag. Moving to the day of the fight if he had less than an hour from the time he arrived in the arena to the time he was going to be getting his name called, there is no way he got drug tested. From the looks of things from the inflated arms to the way he came out to start the fight. I saw Conor McGregor on performance enhancers. I don’t know if anyone else saw the same but I suspect multiple of levels of foul play from conors side to Dana and USADA leading up to this fight

snippet.textDisplay:
I think part of it was that he knew all of that drama wasn't going to affect Cowboy.

Everyone's expectation, including Cowboy's, was to do the same ole, same ole, but I feel like it had to be in Cowboys mind. He had to have spent some time wondering what what the change meant.

I do believe he likes and respects him, but in lieu of the smack talk he hinted about changing things up. Cowboy and his camp had to worry about that because you can't prepare for it, so he sold that I idea by backing it up with a demeanor we've never seen from him before.
It affected everyone that was paying attention. It was more psychological warfare.
